author: COMSOL
description: This introductory model illustrates the action of a magnetohydrodynamics pump. A moving magnetic field is created by three-phase coils, and the contrary induced magnetic field due to eddy currents in the liquid creates a repelling force on the liquid in the column, generating motion. This type of induction pump is used in for example high temperature cooling systems, where the lack of moving parts, and the pumped liquid being kept in a hermetically sealed system, are clear advantages.
label: magnetohydrodynamics_pump.mph
